    "lat": 40.703281,
    "lng": -73.995085,
    "title": "Fulton Ferry",
    "year": null,
    "story": "The Fulton Ferry station was a station on the demolished BMT Fulton Street Line in Brooklyn, New York City. As the name implies, it was built to serve the Fulton Ferry between the two ferry slips in Brooklyn and Manhattan. The Fulton Street Elevated was built by the Kings County Elevated Railway Company and this station started service on April 24, 1888. The station had 2 tracks and 2 side platforms. It was served by trains of the BMT Fulton Street Line, and until 1920, trains of the BMT Brighton Line. This station was served by steam locomotives between 1888 and 1899.",
    "wikipedia_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fulton_Ferry_station"
