    "year": null,
    "story": "The Amiable Child Monument is a monument located in New York City's Riverside Park. It stands west of the southbound lanes of Riverside Drive north of 122nd Street in Morningside Heights, Manhattan. It is a monument to a small boy who died in a fall down the adjacent steep bluff, in what was then an area of country homes near New York City. One side of the monument reads: “Erected to the Memory of an Amiable Child, St. Claire Pollock, Died 15 July 1797 in the Fifth Year of His Age.” The monument was erected above St Claire's grave by George Pollock, who was either the boy's father or his uncle. It is across the street from Grant's Tomb.",
